title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom Built Zombie AR15
postcontent:
This is a brand new build that I just completed. I used a Spikes Tactical Zombie Lower with a DPMS parts kit. I replaced the stock grip with a Magpul MIAD Grip and I installed a standard A2 Butt Stock with an internal storage compartment. The Buffer also has some wadding stuffed inside with the weights to keep rattling down. This lower was then mated to a Bravo Company Mid-Length Upper with a 1:7", chrome lined, Magnetic Particle tested barrel, fitted with a standard A2 Bird Cage Flash Hider. Inside the upper is a Bravo Company Bolt Carrier with a CMMG bolt and pin which is also MP tested. Then I added the Magpul Mid Length MOE Handguard which comes with three rails. A 5 slot on the front bottom which is holding the Harris Bi-Pod via a MAKO bi-pod adapter, a 9 slot rail at the rear holding the EMA Vertical Fore Grip (w/ battery storage) and an empty 9 slot at the 2 O'Clock position available for a light or laser etc.
The Bi-Pod has a canting feature making it easier to shoot on uneven ground and is spring loaded. Adjustable form 9 to 13 inches. 
The scope is an Accu Shot made by Leapers. It is 3-12 x 44mm and has an illuminated reticle. An extra battery is included as well as a color wheel chart as you can scroll through all the colors of the spectrum (Fun!). It comes mounted with low rings and flip up caps.
With this package, I will include the MIAD Grip accessories, a couple papers for the scope and bi-pod, TWO Magpul 20 round PMAG magazines and a Blackhawk 3-Point Universal SWIFT Sling that comes with various attachment options. 

This AR15 was just built and I have not fired any rounds through it as I want to keep it in brand new condition. Yes, that means you will have to zero it but I'm sure most won't complain. 
And please take into consideration manual labor, shipping costs, time, love and finesse with the price tag. Thank You!

title: For Sale:  Yugoslavian SKS 7.62 x 39mm w/bayonet and grenade launcher
postcontent:
Hey there! Looking to sell my good old SKS!
She fires true and I love the gun, but I live in the city and will be moving soon and don't need to take her with me. 
As stated, this is the NATO style Yugoslavian SKS. It fires 7.62 x 39mm rounds. It has a foldable bayonet and also a 22mm grenade launcher barrel attachment. (This shoots old style grenades, not the standard 40mm shot today.) It is gas operated,semi-automatic, and does have the sites attached for the grenade launcher. It includes a stock wrap that holds 20 bullets. The banana clip is not the standard internal magazine and does detach. It is a 15 shot clip. 
Gun has been cleaned once and has mainly sat since. Shot multiple times but not often. She is a well made, well-greased, older, quality weapon that shoots accurately with almost no recoil. 
In the back of the barrel is a circle you can put your finger into with a spring inside. These guns have a special cleaning kit you can put into this spring-loaded storage area. Very-handy, but I do not have the kit unfortunately.

Learn all about my gun here:

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SKS

View my photos here:

http://www.flickr.com/photos/64468888@N04/

Feel free to shoot me an email if you're interested!
Thanks for your time!
-Jake

.40 S&W, Chromed Barrel, steel construction, DA/SA and a VERY cool "tri-action" system.

The tri-action essentially allows for the hammer to be laid down for carry, but with a near-instant return to single-action upon trigger pressure. For an example, see this video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P89vfQUJVCQ

Very accurate little gun (I'm much more accurate with this than I am my M&P or Kahr), with an absolutely amazing trigger pull in single-action.

This has been a great winter carry piece, but with the pickup of a new Kahr for summer carry, I'm itching to trade for something new.
